comments.body: Seria possível coletar esse espécime, já que está morto?
@wolfgang_wuster Populations from Vitoria da Conquista and vicinities are recovered as a basal lineage of B. jararacussu. Also different in morphology. Not B. pirajai at all.

@omarentiauspe I didn't see your comment - is this the same lineage also found in Santa Teresa ES? I hadn't seen evidence of them reaching that far north. This is pretty close to the type locality of *B. pirajai* in Ilhéus...

Not really, as far as I know. There's a gap for B. jararacussu on N Espírito Santo, followed by an isolated population from NE Minas and S Bahia, which belongs to this new species. This can be seen in the Atlas of Nogueira et al. 2019.
